<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,466,492]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Farré &amp; Pujade-Villar, 2007" authorityName="Farré &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2007" box="[633,915,466,491]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Scutimica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transcarinata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[633,915,466,491]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Scutimica transcarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[923,989,466,492]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[923,989,466,492]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the following characters: mesoscutum, which is smooth in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="♀ Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2007" box="[444,532,506,531]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Scutimica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis box="[444,532,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and strongly transversally carinated in 
<taxonomicName authority="Farré &amp; Pujade-Villar, 2007" authorityName="Farré &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2007" box="[998,1187,506,531]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Scutimica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transcarinata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[998,1187,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. transcarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1196,1262,506,532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1196,1262,506,532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; the scutellum has a strong depressed area in the central part in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="♀ Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2007" box="[734,823,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Scutimica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis box="[734,823,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while in 
<taxonomicName authority="Farré &amp; Pujade-Villar, 2007" authorityName="Farré &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2007" box="[938,1127,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Scutimica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transcarinata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[938,1127,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. transcarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1137,1204,546,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1137,1204,546,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
it is not depressed; median mesoscutal line present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="♀ Ros-Farre &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2007" box="[555,643,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Scutimica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis box="[555,643,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Farré &amp; Pujade-Villar, 2007" authorityName="Farré &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2007" box="[807,996,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Scutimica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transcarinata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[807,996,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. transcarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1004,1070,586,612]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1004,1070,586,612]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1372]" box="[198,946,626,652]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,454,626,652]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description. Length.</emphasis>
Females: 2.8 to 3.0 mm; males unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,340,666,692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head, antennae, mesosoma and metasoma medium brown. Legs light brown except for metatibia and metatarsi, which are darker. In the 
<typeStatus box="[719,823,706,732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">paratype</typeStatus>
, lower face, mesoscutum and scutellum light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,272,746,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Head.</emphasis>
Frons with piliferous punctures, face with transversal carinae and piliferous punctures. Malar furrow conspicuous and coriaceous. Vertex in dorsal view with small piliferous punctures, posteriorly with strong to weak oblique carinae. Occiput smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,313,866,892]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Antenna.</emphasis>
Long and filiform. Antennal formula: 14(5): 6(5): 13(5): 12.5(5): 12(5): 12(5): 12(5): 11(5): 10.5(5): 10(5): 9(5): 9(5): 14(5). Placoid sensilae present, abundant from F1 to F11.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,337,946,972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Pronotum in lateral view with noticeable transversal carinae on dorsal half, not prominent dorsally. Pronotal plate with small piliferous punctures. Mesoscutum smooth and shiny. Parascutal sulcus very wide. Median mesoscutal sulcus and notauli straight, reaching first 1/3 of mesoscutum, notauli slightly wider than median mesoscutal sulcus. Median mesoscutal line very strong. Antero-admedian lines narrow and extremely weak, reaching the dorsal 1/3 of mesoscutum, parallel. Lateral basal impression fairly strong. Mesoscutum, seen in lateral view, convex. Scutellar foveae fairly deep, transversal. Scutellar disc with strong depressed area in center, delimited by lateral scutellar carinae, which are well developed; few transversal carinae at sides, between lateral scutellar carinae and lateral margins. Mesoscutum 1.2 to 1.4 of scutellum length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,266,1372]" box="[198,1088,1266,1292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,324,1266,1292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Forewing.</emphasis>
Radial cell 2.3 to 2.5 times longer than wide; R2 almost straight.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
